<br>
There are some okay items that come from tailoring but they're all &gt;250 skill items and beyond 131 skill (when Crystalline Silk armor trivials) Tailoring becomes very tedious.<br>
<br>
Jewelcraft is really the most practical tradeskill.  With JC you can make great stuff that you will actually use for the most part and are not easily replaced later on (who doesn't have a set of BD gear or diamond rings?).  Problem is from a mage standpoint is, making magic jewelry is outside oru abilities unless we get an Enchanter to enchant the metals for us.<br>
<br>
Granted skills like Fletching *are* useful, but for the classes it's useful for they have normally already worked the skill for themselves.  The items that come from high end tradeskills though for the most part, as a magician, are not very useful.  If you enjoy working tradeskills though why not? =)<br>
<br>
Tailoring (131), Baking (165), Fletching (200), Jewelcraft (200), Smithing (167), Brewing (200), Research (145)<br>
<br>
As you can see... I have a little background in them skills ^_^  Was able to make all my level 49 spells with low research.  Also, completed shawl 7 with 131 tailorign - <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> a suggested path though ;)<br>
